From: Juliana Taiwo-Obalonye, Abuja Staff of the Aso Rock Presidential Villa, in Abuja, on Thursday, offered special prayer for the quick recovery of President Muhammadu Buhari’s son, Yusuf, who was injured, on Tuesday night, in a bike crash around Gwarimpa in the Federal Capital Territory. The prayer session which was held immediately after the (Asr) afternoon prayer, was led by the Chief Imam of Aso Rock Mosque, Sheik Abdulwahid Suleiman. Suleiman, who prayed for God’s guidance and protection of the first family and all Nigerians, also prayed for peace and tranquility in the country. Yusuf is still being treated at Cedarcrest Hospital, located in Gudu District, Abuja which services include Intensive Care and surgery.